This paper discusses privacy concerns related to the streaming of big data from IoT devices, particularly mobile platforms like pedestrians and cars, in the context of smart cities. It proposes a privacy-preserving architecture for data collection and analysis, which involves managing and controlling data exchanges. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper also discusses the challenges of managing and processing large volumes of data in real-time, which are relevant to these sub-categories.
